body:
I get errors when rustc tries to build LLVM:

```
In file included from /home/shum/src/rust/rust-a/src/llvm/include/llvm/IR/Module.h:23:0,
                 from /home/shum/src/rust/rust-a/src/llvm/include/llvm/IR/ModuleSummaryIndex.h:27,
                 from /home/shum/src/rust/rust-a/src/llvm/include/llvm/Bitcode/BitcodeReader.h:20,
                 from /home/shum/src/rust/rust-a/src/llvm/tools/llvm-cat/llvm-cat.cpp:17:
/home/shum/src/rust/rust-a/src/llvm/include/llvm/IR/Attributes.h:74:14: fatal error: llvm/IR/Attributes.gen: No such file or directory
     #include "llvm/IR/Attributes.gen"
              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
compilation terminated.
make[2]: *** [tools/llvm-cat/CMakeFiles/llvm-cat.dir/build.make:63: tools/llvm-cat/CMakeFiles/llvm-cat.dir/llvm-cat.cpp.o] Error 1
make[1]: *** [CMakeFiles/Makefile2:17280: tools/llvm-cat/CMakeFiles/llvm-cat.dir/all] Error 2
```

As well as several errors along the lines of

```
/nix/store/b0zlxla7dmy1iwc3g459rjznx59797xy-binutils-2.28.1/bin/ld: cannot find -lLLVM
collect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status
make[2]: *** [tools/llvm-config/CMakeFiles/llvm-config.dir/build.make:96: bin/llvm-config] Error 1
make[1]: *** [CMakeFiles/Makefile2:15890: tools/llvm-config/CMakeFiles/llvm-config.dir/all] Error 2
make[1]: *** Waiting for unfinished jobs....
```

The environment I'm building in is defined by this default.nix, which lists all and only the dependencies listed in the README:

```
with import <nixpkgs> {}; {
  rustcEnv = stdenv.mkDerivation {
    name = "rustc-env";
    buildInputs = [
      gcc
      cmake
      curl
      git
      python2
      gnumake
    ];
  };
}
```
